<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5676] Uninstall should throw an exception if called while the bundle is starting or stopping</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5676</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If uninstall is called on a bundle from within the thread that is currently starting or stopping the bundle (i.e., the bundle is trying to change its own state while holding its bundle lock) we currently just let the uninstall happen. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That can cause the bundle to be delivered to other bundles as starting or stopping or active while actually being uninstalled already. Instead, we should detect this situation and throw an IllegalStateException instead (as per spec).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
